# LLM Routing Standards

## Model Selection
- Use env_spec.py to define model ARNs per mode
- offline mode: use stub/mock LLM (no API calls)
- local-live mode: use dev Bedrock inference profile
- prod mode: use prod Bedrock inference profile

## Fallback Logic
- Implement retry with exponential backoff
- Log all LLM call failures with request ID
- Fall back to cheaper model on rate limit errors
- Never retry on authentication errors

## Cost Controls
- Log token usage per request
- Set max_tokens limits per use case
- Monitor daily spend via CloudWatch metrics

## Safety
- Never log full prompts in production (may contain PII)
- Redact sensitive fields before sending to LLM
- Validate LLM responses before using in business logic

## JSON Parsing
- When parsing structured JSON from LLMs, always strip markdown code fences (` ```json ` / ` ```JSON ` / ` ``` `) and surrounding prose before parsing. LLMs frequently wrap JSON in fences even when instructed not to. Use a robust extraction pattern: strip fences first, then find outermost braces, then parse.

## Sampling Parameters
- For Bedrock Claude models, never send both `temperature` and `top_p` in the same request — the API rejects it. Send `temperature` only; omit `top_p`.
